            <!-- What IS Keto? -->
            <div class="paragraph row justify-content-center">
                <div class="col-8 text-center">
                    <h2 class="about-header">What is the keto diet?</h2>

                    <!-- Fading Divider, Shortered and Centered -->
                    <div class="row justify-content-center">
                        <div class="col-8 justify-content-center">
                            <span class="divider mb-3"></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="about-body">
                        The keto diet is a low carb, moderate protein, high fat diet. The goal of
                        of the diet is each a low enough amount of carbohydrates so that your body enters
                        the state of ketosis.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- What Is Ketosis? -->
            <div class="paragraph row justify-content-center">
                <div class="col-8 text-center">    
                    <h2 class="about-header justify-content-center">What is ketosis?</h2>
                    <!-- Fading Divider, Shortered and Centered -->
                    <div class="row justify-content-center">
                        <div class="col-8 justify-content-center">
                            <span class="divider mb-3"></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="about-body">
                        The bodies primary fuel source is glucose, as it is the easiest molecule for your
                        body to convert to energy.

                        While eating carbohydrates, your body will produce glucose and insulin. Glucose
                        for your energy needs, and insulin to process the glucose in your bloodstream.

                        When you are not feeding your body the required amount of carbohydrates for it 
                        to rely primarily on glucose, your body will enter the state of ketosis in order
                        to meet its energy needs by consuming body fat.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Why Ketosis? -->
            <div class="paragraph row justify-content-center mb-4">
                <div class="col-11 col-md-10 text-center">    
                    <h2 class="about-header justify-content-center">Why Ketosis?</h2>
                    <!-- Fading Divider, Shortered and Centered -->
                    <div class="row justify-content-center">
                        <div class="col-8 justify-content-center">
                            <span class="divider mb-3"></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>            
                    <p class="about-body">
                        Being in ketosis comes with numerous health benefits, especially in today's
                        culture full of process foods and added sugars everywhere you look.

                        It was originally created in 1923 by Dr. Russell Wilder at the Mayo Clinic as 
                        an effective way to treat epilepsy. It fell out of favor after epilepsy medicines
                        hit the market, however it is still used today for medication resistant epilepsy.
                
                        Not only does the ketogenic diet promote weight loss, it can help treat a number of
                        common ailments in today's age caused by our cultures poor dietary options and education in many areas.
                
                        However, the benefits do not stop there! There are many secondary benefits that attract
                        all kinds of people to the keto life style.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
